{{Infobox song | title = When The Fleet Comes Sailing Home | English_title = | comment = | image = | caption = Sheet Music cover | alt = | original_artist = | recorded_by = | performed_by = | written = | Released = <!-- {{Start date|YYYY|MM|DD}} --> | Published = 1918 | Length = <!-- {{Duration|m=MM|s=SS}} --> | Writer = Carl M. Legg | Composer = Jay Flanagan | Language = English | Form = }} '''When The Fleet Comes Sailing Home''' is a [[World War I]] song written by Carl M. Legg and composed by Jay Flanagan.<ref>{{cite book |last1=Vogel |first1=Frederick G. |date=1995 |title=World War I Songs: A History and Dictionary of Popular American Patriotic Tunes, with Over 300 Complete Lyrics |location=Jefferson |publisher=McFarland & Company, Inc. |page=272 |isbn=0-89950-952-5}} {{OCLC | 32241433}}</ref> The song was first published in 1918 by Songland Music in [[Brooklyn, NY]]. The sheet music cover depicts a mother, wife, and son in uniform waving at an arriving transport ship.<ref>{{cite book |last=Parker |first=Bernard S. |year=2007 |title=World War I Sheet Music Vol 2. |location=Jefferson |publisher=McFarland & Company, Inc. |page=782 |isbn=0-7864-2799-X |oclc=71790113}}</ref>
The sheet music can be found at the [[Pritzker Military Museum & Library]].<ref>Flanagan, T. Jay, and Carl M. Legg. 1918. ''When the fleet comes sailing home''. Brooklyn (549 Kosciusko St., Brooklyn, N.Y.): Songland Music Pub. Co.{{OCLC|79690734}}</ref>
